situation: A prestressed cantilever beam 460mm wide has an overall depth of 630mm. The beam is to carry a concentrated live load of 40kN at the free end. Unit weight of concrete = 24kN/m<sup>3</sup>. The prestressing force is 1500kN and applied at an eccentricity of "e" above the neutral axis of the beam.

subquestions.question: What is the stress at the top fibers of the beam at the free end when e=100mm, in MPa?
What is the stress at the bottom fibers of the beam at the free end when e=100mm, in MPa?
What is the stress at the bottom fibers of the beam at the fixed end when e=120mm, in MPa?
What is the stress at the top fibers of the beam at the free end when e=120mm, in MPa?
What is the required eccentricity (in mm) such that the stress at the top fibers of the beam at the fixed end is zero?
